It will increase the income of the budget, will create new jobs, some branches will begin to extend, some to accustom quicker, the contribution to GDP growth will be made.
Dependence of Russia on the foreign food will decrease several times, however, not at once", - the expert notes.
Earlier Russian enterprises often could not break through on counters of local shops because of the high competition from foreign analogs.
Now, after embargo introduction, this niche was freed and it is possible to breathe sigh of relief.
But you should not forget that after all necessary coordination and sanitary inspections will enter foodstuff from the countries of Latin America, Turkey and Serbia the Russian market.
In other words, "moment of calm" when former players already left came now, and new did not come yet.
Nearly a month later it is possible to speak about the increased demand for domestic raw materials, and also increase in prices for finished goods", - the first Vice-president of the all-Russian public organization "Russian Club of Financial Directors", PhD Econ. Tamara Kasyanova told AiF.ru.
Without a doubt, the idea to sell at least 50% of the Russian foodstuff in each category will allow to assign sector to local producers.
In that case they will compete with each other, but not with goods which by subsidies of other state, cost cheaper.
In other words, fight for the buyer will be developed between the companies working under uniform laws of branch.
On the other hand, Kasyanova notes, the Russian producers are capable to satisfy 50% of internal needs of compatriots far not in all respects.
And in this situation distribution networks should "hold out" a share of the Russian goods to a half of the range.
In this regard fears increase that low-quality goods will get on the shelves.
Perhaps, under the guise of manufactured in Russia foreign products with the changed labels will be delivered", - the expert adds.
Negative effect of introduction of quotas large distribution networks, especially will feel those, it is more favorable to them to cooperate with importers.
It is logical that also foreign suppliers as demand for their production will decrease in this situation will suffer.
Litvinenko does not exclude that the law on quotas for domestic goods can have impact also on consumers.
The matter is that some products of the Russian production can be of a lower quality than import analogs whereas shops are able to inflate the prices of the second, as on scarce goods.
Economists started talking about the idea of import substitution forgotten at the beginning of the 2000th years in February of this year because of continuous devaluation of ruble again.
Now against the difficult relations with the West the question of refusal of import products becomes even more relevant.
The law is designed to oblige retailers when forming orders to suppliers to reckon with domestic manufacturers.
Then we will much quicker and more surely go on the way of import substitution, and the system of planning of production by necessary types of production will be created in shorter terms", - the deputy Oleg Nilov says.
Especially effective the mechanism of quoting will be for those agricultural sectors where potential is especially high, for example, in dairy branch where the share of import made 25%.
Our farmers are really capable to cover counters of the Russian shops completely.
Besides, also meat production can receive a powerful boost.
It is known that the greatest share of import remains on beef - from 30% to 35%.
It turns out, 65-70% are the share after all of the Russian production", - Kasyanova argues.
Experts hold the opinion that introduction of quotas for domestic goods will promote import substitution and can accelerate this process.
However this initiative, in itself to import substitution, will not bring as the package of measures is for this purpose necessary, Litvinenko is sure.
Anyway 50% of the sold goods according to this initiative all the same can be brought from abroad, so, full import substitution will not happen, but considerable steps in this direction will be done.
Besides it is not enough to establish quotas, it is necessary to arrange in the country production of domestic goods that to execute these quotas.
These quotas just will also provide such guarantees", - the expert states.
Out of time made diagnosis and lack of access to optimum treatment mean that ovarian cancer in rural areas kills more
Angelina Jolie and her brother James published video of memory of their late mother who died of ovarian cancer in 2007.
The women stitching in rural areas of Australia face higher risk of death from ovarian cancer, than living in the cities.
Researchers analysed medical records of more than 1100 Australian women with the diagnosis "ovarian cancer" in 2005, having found out that only 35 percent lived five years after the diagnosis was made.
The leading researcher Susan Jordan from QIMR Berghofer Medical research institute reported that probability to die during research 20 percent higher at those who live in regions and the remote districts of the state, than at those who live in urban areas.
SMALL RESEARCH: New drugs can slow down lung cancer and ovarian cancer
Researchers tracked a medical way of women in seven years.
Doctor Jordan told that age of the woman at the time of diagnosis, the ovarian cancer type, existence of the current diseases and the socioeconomic status also influenced probability of a survival.
Women of more advanced age and those who had a cancer in later stage at the time of diagnosis had the lowest survival rates.
For those who lived in regions or the remote districts of the state the probability to die during research was 20 percent higher, than for those who lived in urban areas.
Though research was not intended to define why the women living outside the cities more likely die of ovarian cancer, doctor Jordan assumed that out of time made diagnosis and lack of access to optimum treatment - possible factors.
"This disease is best of all treated by the surgeons specializing in gynecologic oncology, and they, mainly, are in big cities", she told.
Despite improvement of quality of telemedicine services to reduce influence of distance, she assumed that increase in number of services on departure which will allow experts to treat women closer to the house and programs of support of the people passing treatment is far from the house, can help.
Doctor Jordan told that irrespective of a geographical position, research revealed that long life expectancy among women with ovarian cancer was rare, having emphasized need for more effective strategy of treatment and prevention.
The research financed by Rio Tinto Ride to Conquer cancer will be published in Medical Journal of Australia today.
In March, 2012, at the age of 33 years, young mother with Gold Coast Elisha Neave was told that she has an aggressive form of ovarian cancer.
