For the first time the NFC function was presented in 2004 within cooperation of the companies Sony, Nokia, Philips Semiconductors and more than one hundred other companies which entered so-called NFC Forum - association on advance of this technology.
The first phone with NFC was released by the Nokia company in 2006.
The first smartphone on Android with the NFC function - Samsung Nexus S - was presented in 2010.
In May, 2011 Google presented the Google Wallet system allowing users to link cash cards to the account in Google and to pay off by means of the smartphone on Android.
However, the American experts emphasize that, despite large investments of the hi-tech companies into advance of the NFC technology, the American retailers still carefully treat an innovation and not too willingly spend money for the equipment of the shops such systems.
