The anger was the most universal and functional emotion of the person
The angry facial expression is biologically universal for mankind, and each body participating in its creation and group of muscles is not casual, and is an additional tool of expression of power and threat, scientists of Australia and the USA found out.
They told about the opening in the Evolution and Human Behavior magazine, and shortly about them it is possible to read in the press release of the Californian university in Santa Barbara.
The angry look - the eyebrows shifted and lowered down extended to the thin line of a lip, the inflated nostrils - is identical in all cultures, and even blind people from the birth children, never its seeing do it, the leading author of research Aaron Sell notes.
Within the large research project devoted to the anger nature, scientists found out that there was this emotion for effective conducting disputes during the conflict.
The more physical damage one person can cause to another, the it is more at it than opportunities dictate the terms, and it informs of it the interlocutor by means of anger.
Researchers found confirmations and other hypothesis: physically strong people become angry more often and pass to a manhandling, consider themselves to have the right to impose others unprofitable conditions for them, and also prefer power methods of the solution of the conflicts to peace.
Making a start from the fact that the anger is first of all "emotion of the bargaining", scientists decided that the movements of each of seven groups of muscles creating an angry facial expression have to represent the angry individual more powerful and dangerous in the opinion of the interlocutor - and by that to force to agree as soon as possible with his conditions in order to avoid the conflict.
For check of this hypothesis researchers simulated on the computer of the person where was present or there was no each of seven elements of the angry person, and showed them to informants.
Though the lowered eyebrows or the chin pushed forward separately did not do a face angry, stronger physically participants of research recognized the person represented with such lines unanimously.
The anger of the person, as well as at animals, expresses threat: the exaggerated manifestation of own force forcing to agree and obey.
The person inflates nostrils and purses lips with the same purpose, as a frog who is inflated, or a baboon which shows the canines.
"The anger "is started" by refusal of the interlocutor to accept a situation, and the person takes the form which is most effectively showing to the opposite side of a consequence of this refusal at once.
But the most amazing - that any of components of the angry person is not any, all of them express same", - the anthropologist John Tooby noted.
Suggested to allocate to the Ministry of Telecom and Mass Communications 250 million rubles of Crimea television and radio broadcasting company
Suggested to allocate to the Ministry of Telecom and Mass Communications in 2014 from the federal budget 250 million rubles of autonomous non-profit organization Crimea television and radio broadcasting company.
It is stated in the draft of the government resolution prepared by department with which Lenta.ru got acquainted.
According to the explanatory note to the project, a subsidy from the federal budget will are directed "to a covering of expenses on creation of conditions for large-scale information illumination of a social and economic situation and development of modern information space in the territory of the Republic of Crimea, including acquisition of the equipment".
In particular, on the allocated money it is supposed to convert the hardware and studio block, video walls, the central equipment room and the video server room.
Also acquisition of mobile television station and the satellite transmitter is planned.
Besides, from the allocated funds the company will pay use of the fiber-optic communication link (FOCL) and carrying out repair of system of power.
Subsidies will be provided within the means of the federal budget provided for the Ministry of Telecom and Mass Communications.
The state television and radio broadcasting company Crimea is created in 1959, carries out broadcasting in seven languages: Ukrainian, Russian, Crimean Tatar, German, Greek, Bulgarian and Armenian.
Today coverage by a television signal of broadcasting company makes more than 75 percent of the territory of the peninsula.
In 2011 Crimea television and radio broadcasting company obtained the license for television broadcasting in a digital format.
